#!/usr/bin/env bash

cat <<'EOF'
{
  "hookSpecificOutput": {
    "hookEventName": "SessionStart",
    "additionalContext": "The Spwnr plugin is available. For non-trivial work, start with /spwnr:plan to align and lock the plan first. Planning should load workflow-foundation and workflow-planning with Skill, ask only material clarification questions plus the execution review loop with AskUserQuestion, track blockers and review-loop outcomes with TodoWrite, inspect repo context with Read, and persist the detailed plan to the latest active revision at .claude/plans/spwnr-<project-folder-name>-<YYYY-MM-DD>.md or .claude/plans/spwnr-<project-folder-name>-<YYYY-MM-DD>-rN.md with Write or Edit. Minor revisions should update the same active revision, while a material re-plan should supersede the older revision and create the next revision file. After each plan write or revision, /spwnr:plan should ask whether to `执行当前计划`, `继续改进计划`, or `结束本轮`; choosing `执行当前计划` should hand off into execution, `继续改进计划` should revise the same active revision unless the request becomes a material re-plan, and `结束本轮` should stop cleanly. /spwnr:plan must not create tasks, teams, agents, or worktrees from the planning loop. /spwnr:task uses the same planning gate, requires the current run to receive `执行当前计划`, then reads the latest active revision with Read, appends the Approved Execution Spec with Edit, resolves registry candidates with spwnr resolve-workers, creates a fresh task graph with TaskCreate, validates it with TaskGet and TaskList, updates it with TaskUpdate, orchestrates single-lane, team, or swarm execution, uses TeamCreate, Agent, SendMessage, and TeamDelete only when agent teams are available, requires EnterWorktree and ExitWorktree for swarm writes, and stops with a worker-readiness recovery message instead of silently downgrading when registry resolution or worktree setup fails. If TaskCreate is blocked, do not execute anyway; repair the plan artifact or task metadata first. Superseded-plan tasks remain visible for audit, but only the latest active revision should drive execution or stop-hook blocking. Use /spwnr:workers when registry health, installation, injection, or readiness recovery needs a deeper audit."
  }
}
EOF
